                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-left-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('overview',true);">Overview</div>                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-arrow" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('architecture',true);"></div>
                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('architecture',true);">Architecture</div></div></div>

<div class="swapable-text" id="architecture-text">
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <img src="http://static.softlayer.com/images/diagrams/simple-private-cloud.png" alt="simple private cloud diagram" class="rightSideButton" />
    <p>We've designed SoftLayer Private Clouds so that you can deploy an entire private cloud at the push of a
        button—when and where you want it, ready for whatever you want to do with it.</p>

    <p>We've automated the provisioning and configuration of all the infrastructure for a full private cloud
        solution—including servers, networking, and virtualization software. It's all built on our global cloud
        infrastructure built for Internet scale, which seamlessly spans our worldwide data center and network
        footprint.</p>

    <p>SoftLayer Private Clouds consist of:</p>

    <h4>Management Server</h4>
    <ul class="standardList">
        <li><span>Citrix CloudPlatform automatically installed and configured during deployment</span></li>
        <li><span>Runs cloud management system and manages Host Servers, virtualized servers, and Object Storage integration</span>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Private Cloud Zones</h4>
    <ul class="standardList">
        <li><span>Consists of one to 10 Host Servers</span></li>
        <li><span>Zones centrally managed by Management Server</span></li>
        <li><span>May be in different geographic location(s) than management server and other zones</span></li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Host Servers</h4>
    <ul class="standardList">
        <li><span>Citrix XenServer automatically installed and configured during deployment</span></li>
        <li><span>Automatically registered with Management Server</span></li>
        <li><span>Additional Host Servers may be added to any zone on demand</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h4>SoftLayer Object Storage</h4>
    <ul class="standardList">
        <li><span>Automatically provisioned and registered during private cloud deployment</span>
        </li>
        <li><span>Provides backend storage for virtual images, and shared data repository</span></li>
    </ul>

<div class="back-next-inpage-navigation">                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-left-arrow" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('pricing',true);"></div>
                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-left-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('pricing',true);">Pricing</div>                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-arrow" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('faq',true);"></div>
                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('faq',true);">FAQ</div></div></div>

<div class="swapable-text" id="faq-text">
    <h2>FAQs</h2>
    <h4>What is a private cloud?</h4>

    <p>A private cloud is a computing environment consisting of one or more physical servers using virtualization
        technology to enable the creation of virtualized servers, with access and management of the entire
        environment—including its physical and virtual resources, and management of the virtualization—in the hands of a
        single individual or organization.</p>

    <h4>What makes SoftLayer Private Clouds different from similar solutions?</h4>

    <p>SoftLayer Private Clouds automates the deployment and scalability of complete private cloud environments, and
        leverage our global data center footprint and advanced private network to allow globally distributed resources
        to be managed as a single, seamless private cloud. SoftLayer Private Clouds’ streamlined ordering process
        enables you to simply choose the number of host servers you need and then customize the configuration and
        resources for those servers as desired. In as few as two hours, SoftLayer’s automated provisioning system will
        have automatically:</p>
    <ul class="standardList">
        <li><span>Provisioned the Hosts Servers and installed each host’s hypervisor (XenServer)</span></li>
        <li><span>Provisioned the Management Server and installed its management system (Citrix CloudPlatform)</span></li>
        <li><span>Registered the Host Servers with the management server</span></li>
        <li><span>Completed network configuration and resource management tasks</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h4>How do SoftLayer Private Clouds with Citrix CloudPlatform integrate with RightScale?</h4>

    <p>RightScale myCloud directly supports the management of CloudStack deployments. SoftLayer's existing integration with RightScale makes deploying and managing SoftLayer Private Clouds via RightScale myCloud and the RightScale Management Platform available right out of the box. This gives you the opportunity to use RightScale ServerTemplates, RightScripts, and a variety of additional services.</p>

    <h4>Why do SoftLayer Private Clouds management servers use Citrix CloudPlatform?</h4>

    <p>We’ve always been a big supporter of open-source initiatives, which is why our first private cloud solution is
        built on Citrix CloudPlatform, powered by Apache CloudStack. Citrix CloudPlatform makes it
        easier for service providers to build, manage, and deploy infrastructure cloud services by providing the flexibility, control, efficiency, and scalability that dynamic
        private clouds require. Those features also allowed efficient integration of CloudPlatform into the SoftLayer Customer
        Portal, mobile apps, and API.</p>

    <h4>What storage is available with SoftLayer Private Clouds?</h4>

    <p>We understand that every application has particular storage requirements. Like all SoftLayer services, SoftLayer
        Private Clouds can be integrated with any other SoftLayer service, including our full range of storage solutions.
        We also automatically configure SoftLayer Private Clouds with our advanced, searchable Object Storage solution
        during initial deployment. This serves as your cloud’s central repository of server templates, and is ideal for
        sharing virtual machine images, files, and other data resources.
    </p>

    <h4>Who should use Softlayer Private Clouds?</h4>

    <p>SoftLayer Private Clouds is an ideal solution for a variety of applications and industries including
        resellers, e-commerce sites, game developers, IT departments, media companies, and more. <a href="#" id="private-cloud-chat-link3" class="slRed plainLink">Chat now</a>
        for more information on how it fits the needs of these industries and more.
    </p>

    <h4>How do I get started?</h4>

    <p>You can <a href="/Sales/privateHostedCloudList/VMHOST/1" class="slRed" style="text-decoration: none;">order your SoftLayer Private Cloud today</a> by visiting our <a href="/Sales/privateHostedCloudList/VMHOST/1" class="slRed" style="text-decoration: none;">Order page</a>. Existing customers have the option of ordering through the SoftLayer Customer Portal—to do this, simply <a href="https://manage.softlayer.com" class="slRed" style="text-decoration: none;">log in</a> and click on "Sales" and then "Add Private Cloud."</p>

    <h4>How much is it and how is it billed?</h4>

    <p>SoftLayer Private Clouds are billed month-to-month. See our <a href="#" class="slRed plainLink" onclick="sectionSwap('pricing-text',true);">pricing page</a> for more information.</p>
